auth {
  mode: oauth2
}

auth:oauth2 {
  grant_type: authorization_code
  callback_url: http://localhost
  authorization_url: https://login.microsoftonline.com/{{tenantId}}/oauth2/v2.0/authorize
  access_token_url: https://login.microsoftonline.com/{{tenantId}}/oauth2/v2.0/token
  client_id: {{cliClientId}}
  client_secret:
  scope: {{apiScope}} openid profile offline_access
  state:
  pkce: true
  credentials_placement: body
  token_placement: header
  token_header_prefix: Bearer
  auto_fetch_token: true
  auto_refresh_token: true
}

docs {
  Collection-level Auth — applied to every request that has `auth: inherit`.

  This is OAuth 2.0 / Authorization Code + PKCE against Microsoft Entra ID
  (Workforce tenant). It produces a v2.0 access token whose audience matches
  the API app registration ClearAI API DEV — the same audience APIM's
  validate-jwt policy accepts.

  Required environment variables (set in environments/dev-apim.bru):

    tenantId       Entra tenant id (Infinite Apps)
    cliClientId    Public client app reg id (ClearAI CLI DEV) — uses PKCE,
                   no client_secret
    apiAudience    Protected API's App ID URI
    apiScope       <apiAudience>/access_as_user — the delegated permission

  CRITICAL: credentials_placement = body. The CLI client is public (no
  client_secret), so Microsoft's token endpoint MUST receive the client_id
  as a form field in the request body, NOT as HTTP Basic Auth. Setting
  this to `basic` breaks with HTTP 400 invalid_request.

  Scopes:
    {{apiScope}}     — the API access scope; sets token aud + scp
    openid           — gives ID-token claims (name, oid)
    profile          — adds upn, preferred_username
    offline_access   — gives a refresh token so Bruno renews silently

  How to use:
    1. Top-right dropdown → select dev-apim
    2. Hit Send on any request — Bruno triggers the browser auth flow
       on first send, then injects the bearer token automatically
    3. Subsequent requests reuse / refresh the token
}
